FBIS4-44027 "drweu122_j_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-122 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Pope To Return to Work Following Hip Accident Pope To Return to Work Following Hip Accident AU2306162094 Paris AFP in English 1525 GMT 23 Jun 94 AU2306162094 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Vatican City, June 23 (AFP) -- Pope John Paul II will officiate in public next Wednesday [29 June] for the first time since he fell and broke his hip two months ago, the Vatican said on Thursday. The pontiff, who spent a month in a clinic after the April 29 fall, has returned to work at the Vatican but has been careful to rest. He will celebrate mass at St Peter's next Wednesday.
